    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The balsam exudate obtained from several North American trees, including the longleaf pine, Pinus palustris, the Cuban pine, Pinus caribaea, and the loblolly pine, Pinus taeda. Gum thus is a thick, yellowish, sticky mass with a characteristic piney odor. It is used as an additive in oil paints, an insecticide, a polish, and as an antiseptic agent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
